He is often referred to as the 'Father of His Country' and played a key role in the American Revolutionary War. Washington was born on February 22, 1732, in Westmoreland County, Virginia, and died on December 14, 1799, in Mount Vernon, Virginia. He is widely regarded as one of the founding fathers of the United States and his leadership during the formative years of the nation was instrumental in shaping its future.
